# Shaffer-Softworks/Openobserve (HACS integration)

## Repos (split 2026-05-20)

| Repo | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| **This repo** — https://github.com/Shaffer-Softworks/Openobserve | HACS integration `custom_components/openobserve/` |
| **Add-on** — https://github.com/Shaffer-Softworks/home-assistant-openobserve-addon | Supervisor `openobserve_log_shipper/` (Fluent Bit → `/_multi`) |

Git remote may still show `sickkick/Openobserve` (redirects to Shaffer-Softworks). Integration v**0.2.0**, release tag `v0.2.0`.

## Integration behavior

- Domain: `openobserve`
- Ingest: `POST /api/{org}/{stream}/_json` (JSON array batches)
- Default streams: `home_assistant_logs`, `home_assistant_events`
- Batching: 50 records or 5s; service `openobserve.flush`; diagnostic sensors
- Brand: `custom_components/openobserve/brand/` (Dashboard Icons open-observe, Apache-2.0)
- HACS: `hacs.json`, `info.md`, `.github/workflows/validate.yaml` (hassfest + HACS, no `ignore: brands`)

## Config flow (HA 2025.12+)

`OpenObserveOptionsFlowHandler` must use `self._config_entry` only. Do **not** set `self.config_entry` or call `super().__init__(config_entry)` (caused 500 / AttributeError).

User-step fields use `TextSelector`, not bare `str`.

